## Improvement conventions

- Every improvement is a Git commit with a clear message.
- Format: `<skill-name>: <what changed>` (e.g., `design-encode: tighten default-override block`)
- System changes: `design: <what changed>`
- Profile changes: `config: <what changed>`

## Please family

`design-please` is one of five please-family frameworks. When the work points beyond design direction and encoding, reach for a sibling.

| Framework | What it does |
|-----------|-------------|
| [strategy-please](https://github.com/yesplease-studio/strategy-please) | Workshop recommendation engine — diagnoses strategic gaps and prescribes the right workshop to run |
| [voice-please](https://github.com/yesplease-studio/voice-please) | Voice and language system — defines how a company sounds, the sibling to design-please |
| [prd-please](https://github.com/yesplease-studio/prd-please) | PRD methodology — translates strategy into structured product specifications and executable tasks |
| [sales-please](https://github.com/yesplease-studio/sales-please) | Deal qualification — WORTH framework for deciding which deals deserve time |

### When to suggest a sibling

| Suggest | When |
|---------|------|
| **strategy-please** | Design discovery surfaces positioning confusion. The user can't describe look-and-feel because brand position is unclear. Design is the symptom; strategy is the fix. |
| **voice-please** | Visual language is set and the user wants matching voice work — or vice versa. Design and voice together operationalize brand experience. |
| **prd-please** | Design Brief is complete and the product needs to be specified. Design direction informs but does not replace the PRD. |
| **sales-please** | Design artifacts exist and the user wants to use them in a pitch deck, one-pager, or sales collateral. Run `design-encode` with that specific artifact in mind. |
